com.stormpath.spring.filter

Class StormpathWrapperFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.stormpath.sdk.servlet.filter.HttpFilter
      • com.stormpath.spring.filter.StormpathWrapperFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.servlet.Filter

    public class StormpathWrapperFilter
extends HttpFilter
    This filter adds Client and Application as attributes to every request in order for subsequent Filters to have access to them. For example, a filter trying to validate an access token will need to have access to the Application (see AuthorizationHeaderAccountResolver)
    Since:
    1.3.0

      • filter

        public void filter(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                   javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response,
                   javax.servlet.FilterChain chain)
            throws Exception
        Description copied from class: HttpFilter
        Same contract as for HttpFilter.doFilter(javax.servlet.ServletRequest, javax.servlet.ServletResponse, javax.servlet.FilterChain), but guaranteed to be invoked only once per request. Default implementation simply invokes chain.doFilter(request, response).
        Overrides:
        filter in class HttpFilter
        Parameters:
        request - incoming ServletRequest
        response - outgoing ServletResponse
        chain - the FilterChain to execute
        Throws:
        Exception - if there is a problem processing the request
